title: Not Gummy at all.More like Jelly or Jam
review: I appreciate the vegan aspect but these gummies are not like fruit snacks or like gummies.Consistency of jelly.If that's your "jam" then you'll enjoy these but I did not.I also have a problem when the seller does not allow me to leave seller feedback for them since I had an issue with the busted packaging and length it took to get to me.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on May 2, 2020
name: S. Johns
title: Do not trust Delivery
review: The bunnies had a nice flavor but we're melted together in the bag and very sticky, which surprised me since I ordered them during the winter season, the main issue I had thought was the time it took to receive the item which was well over a month even though when I placed the order the expected delivery was in two days.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on April 12, 2020
name: KarenVC
title: Sticky & Mushy
review: It tastes like it has fruit juice in it, but the consistency of the product is not good. I hate that they are stuck together and your hands get sticky every time you pull one out of the bag. The taste reminds of those jellies they put inside a boba tea drink. Great in boba tea, but not so great by itself. I think the aftertaste comes from the organic tapioca syrup and organic color (black carrot and blackcurrant).The good is that it doesn't have high fructose corn syrup and it's 70 calories for each individual bag. It's $6.98 for 12 pouches when you get it through Amazon Fresh. I guess it's okay for a healthy snack. It's still in the pantry, and I bought them when we first started getting deliveries for covid-19 a month ago. Let's just say it's good when I want something sweet that's not a billion calories.
